  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a detail-oriented M&E Drafter to prepare and manage technical drawings for mechanical and electrical (M&E) systems. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of M&E systems, proficiency in drafting software, and a commitment to accuracy and efficiency.<br /></p><p>Duty & Responsibilities</p><p><strong>Drafting and Documentation:</strong></p><p>· Prepare detailed technical drawings for mechanical and electrical systems based on project specifications.</p><p>· Ensure drawings are accurate, updated, and adhere to company and regulatory standards.</p><p>· Coordinate with the project team to ensure drawings reflect the design intent.</p><p><strong>Collaboration and Coordination:</strong></p><p>· Work closely with engineers, project managers, and contractors to gather necessary inputs for drafting.</p><p>· Review and revise drawings based on feedback from stakeholders.</p><p>· Ensure timely submission of shop drawings, as-built drawings, and other required documentation.</p><p><strong>Technical Support:</strong></p><p>· Assist in resolving technical issues related to M&E drawings during project execution.</p><p>· Provide technical advice and recommendations to ensure design feasibility.</p><p><strong>Compliance and Quality Control:</strong></p><p>· Ensure all drawings comply with relevant codes, standards, and project requirements.</p><p>Conduct quality checks to verify the accuracy and completeness of drawings.<br /></p><p>Requirements<br /><strong>· Qualifications:</strong> Diploma or Certificate in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or a related field.</p><p><strong>· Experience:</strong> Minimum of 2 years of experience in M&E drafting.</p><p><strong>· Skills:</strong></p><p>o Proficiency in AutoCAD and other drafting software.</p><p>o Strong understanding of M&E systems and construction processes.</p><p>o Attention to detail and ability to interpret technical specifications.</p><p>o Good communication and coordination skills.</p><p><strong>Additional:</strong> Knowledge of BIM software (e.g., Revit)<br /></p><p><br />By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by the company relating to this job application.<br />https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf</p><p>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.<br /></p><p>Shirley Pamela Awah<br />Registration Number: R2196979<br />EA License No: 13C6730 (MCI Consulting Pte Ltd)</p>",
